Interface ModerationFilter


  • public interface ModerationFilter
    Interface to implement a Cusotm Moderation filter. filter priority is defined by service ranking property

    • Method Detail

      • getFilterConstraint

        ConstraintGroup getFilterConstraint(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String[]> predicates)
        A custom ModerationFilter must implement getFilter method and return a valid ConstraintGroup. All constraintgroups will finally run with an AND operator for Moderation Search
        Parameters:
        predicates - Complete map of all the search predicates. Usually, A Custom Moderation Filter is only interested in its own predicate and respective values but having a complete map would help to develop a search filter based on some logical inference using other predicates available.
        Returns:
        ConstraintGroup

      • getSupportedPredicate

        java.lang.String getSupportedPredicate()
        Predicate Name 'namespace:string'. It defines which predicate this filter supports e.g. social:flagging
        Returns:
        String fully qualified predicateName
